About this item

  • 【PSU Extension Cable Kit】1x24 Pin ATX Extension Cable (for Motherboard), 1x (4+4) Pin EPS Cable (for CPU), 2 x 6+2-Pin PCI-e Cable and 2 x 6-Pin PCI-e Cable (for GPU), supplied two sets of cable combs, compatible with all power supply cables (must be connected to the power cable, not to the power supply)
  • 【Upgraded 16AWG】Different from 18AWG extension cables on the market, Asiahorse pc cable extension use an upgraded 16AWG pure copper tinned wire that can hold up to 1000W current while resistant high temperature, effectively solving the problem of power cords heating due to the use of high power products, making the power supply safer and more stable.
  • 【Triple Layer Sleeved Design】Using a high-density PET braided mesh tube on the outside and the inner double-layer structure, this power supply cables has conductivity and low impedance, making it soft and easy to bend and these cables will not sag, shrink or swell once molded.
  • 【Cable Management Simper】Comes with two sets of combs: Black and transparent black with a length of 30cm, this braided psu cables are easily solving the problem of insufficient length of the original wires and beautifying the internal space of the case.
  • 【Risk Free Procurement】we focus on the raw materials quality management, plug compatibility, conductor conductivity, wire flexibility and service life, in order to providing every customer with the best products. We provided 1 years of free replacement service and 7*24-hour customer service. Welcome to contact us.

Product Description

2*6+2Pin and 2*6Pin PCI-E Cables

Designed for 8/6Pin Graphics Cards

Fit for any dual 8/6-pin PCIe connection, delivering up to 600 watts of power For GeForce RTX 4070, RTX 4060 Ti and RTX 4060 with 8-pin interface

Can they be used alone with no other extensions?

They are extensions and not actual modular cables for the power supply, only make extensions to your existing cables

Are these compatible with GeForce RTX 40 Series?

Only support GeForce RTX 4070, RTX 4060 Ti and RTX 4060 with 8-pin interface

Are these sleeves all that is needed for a complete build?

Depends on your system's specifics, this kit includes (1) 4+4Pin connectors for CPU power, (2) 6Pin and (2) 6+2Pin GPU cables, if you have an overclocked card you might need (3) 6+2Pin GPU cables.

Will this work with any power supply?

They are extension, not plug into the power supply itself, so these work with any power supply.

How to choose the psu cable extension kit I want

Check the number of power cables for the CPU and GPU. for 2*CPU cables and 3*8Pin GPU cables, select the 2EPS cable kit. for 1*CPU cables and 2*8Pin GPU cables, select the single EPS cable kit.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

5.0 out of 5 stars Nice quality cable extensions with good looks
Reviewed in the United States on May 19, 2020
Color: White-blackVerified Purchase
These cables feel like they're pretty well constructed, and look really nice to boot. The kit comes with all the cables that would be visible in most PC cases these days.
They are a lot more flexible and easy to work with than i figured they would be, and they are plenty long enough for most PC's I'd imagine. I had more than enough length to get them where i needed in my P600S, and the extra wire wasn't too hard to hide on the backside. They also connect snugly.
The plastic connectors and wires themselves seem nicely manufactured, and they come with 2 packs of wire guides (a pack of black ones, as well as a pack of clear-ish ones).

My only real complaint is with the 24-pin connector, it doesn't appear to seat fully for me. This being said, i don't feel concerned about the plug coming out on it's own for any reason, it is VERY snug in there, and unless you're looking at it from the side you wouldn't even notice its not fully seated.

Overall I'd definitely recommend these cable extensions. They are a good value for the quality, finished look, and really nice color choices.

Color: White-blackVerified Purchase
In my eyes, these PSU cable extensions are nearly PERFECT. I seriously would give these a 4.9/5, really tempting to give it a 5/5.

First off, these cables look absolutely INCREDIBLE! I never thought PSU cables made that much of a difference for aesthetics until I put them in and compared them to my old build. I cannot stress enough, it is a game changer when it comes to looks. They are beautiful! (I had the black and white “zebra” cables, but I was considering all white, all black, and black/gray as well. They all look phenomenal)

I was concerned about quality of material, malleability, strength, etc considering how cheap these cables are (bought them for around $35 but rn they’re on sale for $25 which is a killer deal). These cables are incredibly flexible and move very well! However, they also hold their shape well too.

They’re easy to install, never done it before and I had zero problem.

The cables combs are good looking and pretty easy to install once you get the hang of it (Don’t just force it in, flip it over and try to layer the cables in one at a time. Be patient, take your time so they look good or you’ll regret it later)

The ONLY gripe I have is that they give 3 cable combs for every cable, and while this is surely sufficient, 4 would be better for sure. However I will stress, 3 works just fine! My cables have no awkward bends and look amazing.

Overall, when you look at the cables you can see just how gorgeous they are! Additionally, these cables are something that might not always POP 24/7 and grab everyone’s attention, but it’ll never look ugly and stick out like a soar thumb like regular PSU cables.

4.0 out of 5 stars Great looking cables
Reviewed in the United States on March 19, 2020
Verified Purchase
The only beef I have is not just with these, but the way virtually all of them are manufactured. Please for the love of god someone run shorter leads on the inside or lower row, especially on the main board lead, so we can arch the harness without binding up the lower row. Making it curve off the board, especially the large motherboard connector that has to immediately exit through the case. Which leaves the wires bunched up in spite of hours of painstaking work. Also mine had a few pins simply pop loose from the end connectors with little to no stress on them at all before even getting started. I plan on getting the pin release tool, new pins, and doing this customizing myself.
Other than that, this cable set is really good looking and the wires stay in shape so they don't deform while installing them like their thinner counterparts. The wires are thick, the material they use for the covering won't show dust. The combs fit nicely, are snug, and are fairly easy to install. They came very well packaged with ample wire combs to do almost any kind of install. One of my computer geek bud's saw these and ordered his own that very day.
